# EPM Regression — Ground Truth Manager
## Technical Specification

---

## 1. Overview

A web application for authoring and managing ground truth fixtures used in
EPM orchestrator regression testing. Equity admins and developers use it to:

- Author expected values for each test question (ground truth)
- Browse and filter questions by any dimension
- View a dashboard that slices questions by scope, category, agent, route type,
  and other dimensions
- Import run results from the regression test runner and view pass/fail rates
  across those same dimensions
- Export ground truth to CSV/Excel for use by the test runner

The tool is internal — no authentication required for the initial build.

---

## 2. Tech Stack

| Layer       | Choice                                      |
|-------------|---------------------------------------------|
| Backend     | Python 3.12, FastAPI, Uvicorn               |
| Templates   | Jinja2 (served by FastAPI)                  |
| Styling     | Plain CSS (no frameworks)                   |
| JavaScript  | Vanilla JS for progressive enhancement only |
|             | (form field show/hide, no SPA routing)      |
| Storage     | SQLite via SQLAlchemy (separate DB from      |
|             | the agent session DB)                       |
| DB file     | `regression/ground_truth.db`                |
| Excel export| openpyxl                                    |
| Package mgr | uv                                          |

FastAPI serves Jinja2 HTML templates. Every interaction is a full page load
or a form POST — no fetch/AJAX except where noted. JavaScript is used only
for conditional field show/hide in the add/edit form.

