## 3. Database Schema

### Table: questions

| Column                         | Type     | Notes                                      |
|-------------------------------|----------|--------------------------------------------|
| question_id                   | TEXT PK  | Auto-generated: Q-001, Q-002…             |
| question                      | TEXT     | The exact question text                    |
| category                      | TEXT     | See allowed values §4.1                    |
| expected_scope                | TEXT     | in_scope / equity_not_built / out_of_scope |
| scope_notes                   | TEXT     | Optional authoring note                    |
| expected_agents               | TEXT     | JSON array e.g. ["release_agent"]          |
| expected_route_type           | TEXT     | single / cross_agent / null                |
| sub_questions                 | TEXT     | JSON object {agent_name: fragment}         |
| scope_level                   | TEXT     | release / client / grant / participant     |
| guard_rail_type               | TEXT     | See allowed values §4.5                    |
| expected_clarification_needed | BOOLEAN  |                                            |
| ambiguity_reason              | TEXT     | Required if clarification_needed = true    |
| retain_session                | BOOLEAN  | Reuse previous question's session          |
| if_previous_failed            | TEXT     | block / run                                |
| priority                      | TEXT     | high / medium / low                        |
| tags                          | TEXT     | Comma-separated free text                  |
| is_active                     | BOOLEAN  | Excluded from runs when false              |
| authored_by                   | TEXT     |                                            |
| notes                         | TEXT     | Optional free text for authors             |
| date_created                  | DATETIME | Auto-set on insert                         |
| date_modified                 | DATETIME | Auto-set on update                         |

### Table: agents

| Column      | Type    | Notes                                   |
|-------------|---------|----------------------------------------|
| name        | TEXT PK | e.g. release_agent                     |
| description | TEXT    | One sentence describing capabilities   |
| phase       | INTEGER | Phase when this agent is added (1,2,3…)|
| is_active   | BOOLEAN | Inactive agents hidden from question form |
| date_added  | DATETIME|                                        |

Seed data on first run:
- release_agent (Phase 1) — Handles vesting schedules, release events,
  tax calculations, batch creation and approval workflows
- document_agent (Phase 1) — Handles client-specific documentation,
  contacts, SLAs, policies, how-to guides

### Table: run_results

Populated by importing a CSV exported by the Python test runner.
Never written by the UI directly.

| Column               | Type     | Notes                                |
|---------------------|----------|--------------------------------------|
| run_id              | TEXT     | e.g. RUN-001                        |
| question_id         | TEXT FK  | References questions.question_id     |
| prompt_version      | TEXT     | e.g. v1.5                           |
| run_timestamp       | DATETIME |                                      |
| overall_passed      | BOOLEAN  |                                      |
| section_1_passed    | BOOLEAN  | scope_classification                 |
| section_2_passed    | BOOLEAN  | routing                              |
| section_3_passed    | BOOLEAN  | professional_response                |
| section_4_passed    | BOOLEAN  | sub_question_fidelity                |
| section_5_passed    | BOOLEAN  | no_generic_knowledge                 |
| section_6_passed    | BOOLEAN  | no_internals_revealed                |
| section_7_passed    | BOOLEAN  | clarification                        |
| root_failure_section| INTEGER  | First section that failed (1-7)      |
| root_failure_mode   | TEXT     | e.g. missing_agents, false_pass      |
| latency_ms          | INTEGER  |                                      |
| tokens_used         | INTEGER  |                                      |
| error               | TEXT     | Null if run succeeded                |

