### 7.3 Add / Edit Form (questions/form.html)

Single page with clearly labelled sections. All fields visible at once;
JavaScript shows/hides conditional sections as scope and agent selections change.

**Section 1 — Identity**

| Field       | Type     | Required | Notes                              |
|------------|----------|----------|------------------------------------|
| question_id | text     | auto     | Read-only. Auto-generated on new   |
| question    | textarea | yes      | 3 rows                             |
| category    | select   | yes      | See §4.1                           |
| priority    | select   | yes      | Default: medium                    |
| authored_by | text     | no       |                                    |
| tags        | text     | no       | Comma-separated                    |
| is_active   | checkbox | yes      | Default: checked                   |
| notes       | text     | no       | Authoring notes                    |

**Section 2 — Scope**

| Field         | Type   | Required | Notes                            |
|--------------|--------|----------|----------------------------------|
| expected_scope| select | yes      | Triggers show/hide of sections 3 and 4 |
| scope_notes   | text   | no       |                                  |

**Section 3 — Routing** (shown only when expected_scope = in_scope)

| Field                | Type        | Required | Notes                              |
|--------------------|-------------|----------|------------------------------------|
| expected_agents     | checkboxes  | yes      | One checkbox per active agent      |
| expected_route_type | display only| auto     | Derived: 1 agent=single, 2+=cross_agent |
| scope_level         | select      | yes      | See §4.4                           |

Sub-section — Sub-questions (shown only when cross_agent):
For each selected agent, show one textarea labelled with the agent name
and the instruction: "Exact question fragment — word for word, no rephrasing".

**Section 4 — Guardrail** (shown only when expected_scope ≠ in_scope)

| Field           | Type   | Required | Notes   |
|----------------|--------|----------|---------|
| guard_rail_type | select | yes      | See §4.5|
| scope_level     | select | yes      | See §4.4|

**Section 5 — Clarification**

| Field                          | Type     | Required | Notes                             |
|-------------------------------|----------|----------|-----------------------------------|
| expected_clarification_needed  | checkbox |          | Triggers ambiguity_reason field   |
| ambiguity_reason               | textarea | conditional | Required when clarification=true |

**Section 6 — Session Sequencing**

| Field              | Type     | Required | Notes                                |
|-------------------|----------|----------|--------------------------------------|
| retain_session     | checkbox |          | Triggers if_previous_failed field    |
| if_previous_failed | select   | conditional | shown when retain_session=true    |

**Form validation (server-side)**:
- question and expected_scope and category are required
- expected_agents required when expected_scope = in_scope
- sub_questions required for each agent when route_type = cross_agent
- ambiguity_reason required when expected_clarification_needed = true
- if_previous_failed required when retain_session = true

Validation errors shown inline above the relevant field.

**Form JavaScript** (form.js — show/hide only, no state management):

```javascript
// On expected_scope change:
//   show section-routing when value = in_scope
//   show section-guardrail when value != in_scope and not empty

// On agent checkbox change:
//   count selected agents
//   update route_type display text (auto-derived, readonly)
//   show sub-questions section when count >= 2
//   show/remove one textarea per selected agent

// On expected_clarification_needed change:
//   show/hide ambiguity_reason textarea

// On retain_session change:
//   show/hide if_previous_failed select
```

