## 8. Export Formats

### 8.1 CSV (GET /export/csv)

One row per question. All database columns included.
Arrays (expected_agents) stored as pipe-separated: "release_agent|document_agent"
Objects (sub_questions) stored as JSON string.
Filename: ground_truth_YYYY-MM-DD.csv

### 8.2 Excel (GET /export/excel)

Three sheets using openpyxl:

**Sheet 1: Questions**
Same columns as CSV. Header row bold. Column widths auto-fitted.
Conditional cell colours on expected_scope column (green/amber/red).

**Sheet 2: Agent Registry**
name, description, phase, is_active, date_added

**Sheet 3: Run Results** (empty if no runs imported)
All columns from run_results table.

Filename: epm_regression_YYYY-MM-DD.xlsx

### 8.3 JSON (GET /export/json)

Array of question objects in GroundTruth schema format (compatible with
the Pydantic models in ground_truth.py). Filename: ground_truth.json

