## 12. Key Design Rules

- Every page action is a form POST or a GET — no JavaScript fetch calls.
- JavaScript in form.js does only show/hide of conditional fields.
  It does not manage state, call APIs, or compute values.
- expected_route_type is never stored by the user — it is derived server-side
  from the length of expected_agents before saving.
- question_id is generated server-side on insert (never client-side).
- All validation happens server-side in schemas.py.
  Client-side HTML5 required attributes are a convenience only.
- The agents list in the question form is always read from the agents table
  (is_active=true). Adding an agent in the registry immediately makes it
  available in the form with no code changes.
- Dashboard group_by and run_id filter are GET parameters so the URL is
  shareable and bookmarkable.
- Import of run results never modifies the questions table.
